OL,3,C'Inequitable' mooring charges
OL,4,Cprotested by Guernsey boatowners
OL,6,FThe Guernsey Boatowners Association
OL,7,Fhave presented a petition to the
OL,8,FStates of Guernsey objecting to
OL,9,Fproposed mooring fee increases.
OL,11,FThe petition, which has obtained over
OL,12,F1,200 signatures from local
OL,13,Fboatowners, describes the proposed
OL,14,Fincreases for 2025 and 2026 as
OL,15,F"inequitable to the long-term
OL,16,Fdetriment of the local leisure marine
OL,17,Fuser groups".
