OL,3,C'Inequitable' mooring charges
OL,4,Cprotested by Guernsey boatowners
OL,6,FTheir petition argues provisions at
OL,7,FGuernsey Ports "fall well short of
OL,8,Ffacilities available in other ports"
OL,9,Fand it is not fair for the States to
OL,10,Fcharge for "facilities that are sub-
OL,11,Fstandard and in some instances not
OL,12,Feven provided".
OL,14,FIt adds: "The proposed increases help
OL,15,Ffund the admitted continuous cross-
OL,16,Fsubsidy paid for by all harbour users
OL,17,Fto support the losses incurred at
OL,18,FGuernsey Airport."
