OL,3,C'Inequitable' mooring charges
OL,4,Cprotested by Guernsey boatowners
OL,6,FNick Guillemette, President of the
OL,7,FGuernsey Boatowners Association, says
OL,8,Fthe petition hopes to reduce fees
OL,9,Ffurther and provide boatowners with
OL,10,Fstability for the next couple of years.
OL,12,FHe says: "The petition has already had
OL,13,Fan impact. We had an increase of 25%
OL,14,Fthis year, on average, and that's
OL,15,Falready come down to 8.3% - that's a
OL,16,Fresult of our battling.
OL,18,F"But, at the moment, the yacht brokers
OL,19,Fhave closed their books and they've
OL,20,Fgot an unprecedented number of boats
OL,21,Fthat aren't selling.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G4/6
