OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F387A1734036060
OL,3,C'Inequitable' mooring charges
OL,4,Cprotested by Guernsey boatowners
OL,6,F"People are in a state of turmoil -
OL,7,Fthey don't know whether they can keep
OL,8,Fa boat or not."
OL,10,FNick furthers: "We've suggested that
OL,11,Fthey consider a system for charging
OL,12,Fover a five-year period, rather than
OL,13,Fhitting us with massive increases.
OL,15,F"We want to see an affordable increase
OL,16,Fover the five-year period so that
OL,17,Fpeople know what they're in for.
OL,19,F"They can then decide whether to
OL,20,Fdownsize, or sell their boats, or
OL,21,Fwhatever. That will provide stability."
